text:
Dieter Kemper (11 August 1937 – 11 October 2018) was a German cyclist. He competed professionally between 1961 and 1980. During his career he won one UCI Motor-paced World Championships in 1975, seven European titles and 26 six-day road races. He finished three times in third place at world championships.
Kemper died on 11 October 2018 from bone cancer in Julianadorp, the Netherlands at the age of 81.
